1
00:02:36,000 --> 00:02:39,040
<i>Why wasn't it you standing there?</i>
<i>Why did it have to be Nun?</i>

2
00:02:39,720 --> 00:02:40,760
<i>Did you call me here</i>

3
00:02:40,840 --> 00:02:43,040
<i>to have me take the blame for her?</i>

4
00:02:43,120 --> 00:02:44,800
<i>It's all because of her.</i>

5
00:02:44,880 --> 00:02:47,720
<i>You want to see me die, don't you?</i>

6
00:02:47,800 --> 00:02:50,640
Fine, I'll die right in front of you, Ve!

7
00:02:50,720 --> 00:02:52,840
The divorce papers you wanted.

8
00:02:52,920 --> 00:02:56,800
<i>You'll get everything from Liangsuttha</i>
<i>once the case with my mom is concluded.</i>

9
00:02:56,880 --> 00:03:00,400
Miss Gingploy has filed for a retrial
into the death of Ms. Gingyok.

10
00:03:00,480 --> 00:03:02,480
When compared
to the defendant's fingerprints…

11
00:03:02,560 --> 00:03:03,440
PREVIOUSLY

12
00:03:03,520 --> 00:03:05,920
…the result is negative.

13
00:03:06,000 --> 00:03:07,280
No further questions, Your Honor.

14
00:03:08,480 --> 00:03:10,880
Does the defense have any objections?

15
00:03:12,600 --> 00:03:13,520
No, Your Honor.

16
00:03:24,360 --> 00:03:25,200
Your Honor.

17
00:03:25,280 --> 00:03:29,080
Permission to call another witness
who can explain

18
00:03:29,160 --> 00:03:32,320
why there are no fingerprints
of the defendant on the capsules.

19
00:03:32,840 --> 00:03:34,040
And he is also

20
00:03:34,680 --> 00:03:36,160
a direct accomplice in this case.

21
00:03:37,200 --> 00:03:38,240
Objection.

22
00:03:39,760 --> 00:03:41,600
Calling a surprise witness to testify

23
00:03:41,680 --> 00:03:44,320
could result in an unfair trial.

24
00:03:45,240 --> 00:03:47,200
Previously,
the witness was critically injured.

25
00:03:47,280 --> 00:03:48,960
Now that he's recovered,

26
00:03:49,040 --> 00:03:51,640
he's able to testify in court today.

27
00:03:51,720 --> 00:03:53,360
Permission granted.

28
00:04:18,480 --> 00:04:19,800
<i>Aunt Sorn doesn't know</i>

29
00:04:19,880 --> 00:04:21,720
that your condition has improved, did she?

30
00:04:22,400 --> 00:04:23,680
I told everyone

31
00:04:23,760 --> 00:04:26,520
to let Mrs. Sorn believe
I was in a vegetative state

32
00:04:27,320 --> 00:04:28,760
with no chance of recovery.

33
00:04:28,840 --> 00:04:30,160
Ms. Ve said

34
00:04:30,880 --> 00:04:33,160
only you knew
Ms. Gingyok was being poisoned,

35
00:04:34,400 --> 00:04:36,560
and also the truth
behind Ms. Ve's parents' deaths.

36
00:04:36,640 --> 00:04:37,560
Yes.

37
00:04:38,880 --> 00:04:39,840
I know everything.

38
00:04:40,680 --> 00:04:41,920
Then,

39
00:04:42,920 --> 00:04:44,160
can you come with me?

40
00:04:47,920 --> 00:04:49,880
There were no fingerprints
of the defendant

41
00:04:49,960 --> 00:04:52,720
because I was the one
who replaced all of them myself,

42
00:04:52,800 --> 00:04:54,680
under the defendant's orders.

43
00:04:55,400 --> 00:04:57,120
Why did you follow the defendant's orders

44
00:04:57,200 --> 00:04:59,880
so willingly, without fear?

45
00:04:59,960 --> 00:05:03,640
Because this wasn't
the first time she made me do it.

46
00:05:07,440 --> 00:05:08,800
With Mr. Terdthong,

47
00:05:08,880 --> 00:05:11,440
her late husband,

48
00:05:13,200 --> 00:05:15,040
she had me do the exact same thing.

49
00:05:36,920 --> 00:05:38,280
<i>Her husband</i>

50
00:05:39,160 --> 00:05:41,320
<i>died in the same way,</i>

51
00:05:42,280 --> 00:05:43,840
because she used the same method.

52
00:05:44,800 --> 00:05:48,120
Are you aware that your testimony today

53
00:05:49,000 --> 00:05:50,480
could incriminate you

54
00:05:50,560 --> 00:05:53,400
in this and other cases?

55
00:05:54,000 --> 00:05:55,000
I am.

56
00:05:57,200 --> 00:05:59,920
And I'm willing to accept
all punishment for what I've done.

57
00:06:01,360 --> 00:06:03,280
And I also want the murderer

58
00:06:04,240 --> 00:06:06,120
to be punished accordingly.

59
00:06:06,200 --> 00:06:07,040
It's not true!

60
00:06:07,640 --> 00:06:08,680
You're framing me!

61
00:06:08,760 --> 00:06:10,400
How could you do this to me?!

62
00:06:10,480 --> 00:06:11,600
Defendant.

63
00:06:11,680 --> 00:06:12,800
Compose yourself.

64
00:06:16,160 --> 00:06:19,120
I'm not making this up. Everything I said

65
00:06:19,840 --> 00:06:21,880
is all backed by audio recordings.

66
00:06:22,640 --> 00:06:24,360
In those recordings, she gave orders

67
00:06:24,440 --> 00:06:26,720
to get rid of Mrs. Kitinee

68
00:06:27,720 --> 00:06:29,360
and her daughter, Hathai, as well.

69
00:06:35,240 --> 00:06:37,400
If you can get rid of those two,

70
00:06:38,000 --> 00:06:40,240
Mr. Terd will be easy to deal with.

71
00:06:40,840 --> 00:06:42,440
Once they're all dead,

72
00:06:43,480 --> 00:06:46,160
it'll just be the two of us.

73
00:06:46,240 --> 00:06:48,400
No more hiding. No more running.

74
00:06:49,000 --> 00:06:50,560
Can you do this for me?

75
00:06:53,600 --> 00:06:56,960
For you, I'd do anything.

76
00:06:57,040 --> 00:06:59,280
I believed her words.

77
00:07:01,400 --> 00:07:03,400
But it never came true.

78
00:07:04,320 --> 00:07:06,560
I served her loyally for years,

79
00:07:07,160 --> 00:07:08,480
always hoping

80
00:07:09,200 --> 00:07:11,800
that she would appreciate
and value what I did.

81
00:07:15,240 --> 00:07:16,960
But that day never came.

82
00:07:17,680 --> 00:07:19,360
She ordered to have me eliminated

83
00:07:19,960 --> 00:07:21,400
the moment she had Singha to help her.

84
00:07:21,480 --> 00:07:23,600
That opened my eyes. The truth is,

85
00:07:24,880 --> 00:07:27,000
the defendant never loved anyone.

86
00:07:27,080 --> 00:07:28,880
Not even her own daughter.

87
00:07:30,040 --> 00:07:33,480
She sent her to marry a horrible man
just for her own benefit.

88
00:07:34,520 --> 00:07:35,520
Objection.

89
00:07:36,560 --> 00:07:39,040
This testimony is irrelevant to the case.

90
00:07:39,560 --> 00:07:42,240
Please speak only on case-related matters.

91
00:07:43,040 --> 00:07:44,120
I have to say it.

92
00:07:50,240 --> 00:07:52,200
Because I won't let my daughter

93
00:07:54,160 --> 00:07:56,360
suffer that kind of fate again,

94
00:08:00,440 --> 00:08:03,000
not from a selfish mother like this woman.

95
00:08:05,440 --> 00:08:08,320
That's not true, Nun. Don't listen to him.

96
00:08:08,960 --> 00:08:12,160
It's not true. Don't listen to him, Nun.

97
00:08:12,240 --> 00:08:14,400
Nun. Nun!

98
00:08:14,480 --> 00:08:16,200
- Nun, don't listen to him!
- Defendant!

99
00:08:16,280 --> 00:08:17,840
- Nun, that's not true!
- Defendant.

100
00:08:17,920 --> 00:08:19,760
This is your final warning.

101
00:08:19,840 --> 00:08:21,240
Control yourself.

102
00:08:22,600 --> 00:08:23,960
Please get a hold of yourself.

103
00:08:31,520 --> 00:08:32,400
Nun.

104
00:08:36,200 --> 00:08:37,200
Ki.

105
00:08:38,960 --> 00:08:41,320
Uncle Pat… Uncle Pat is my father?

106
00:08:42,080 --> 00:08:44,200
Is he my father?

107
00:08:44,720 --> 00:08:45,560
Nun.

108
00:08:46,600 --> 00:08:50,440
What Uncle Pat said is all true.

109
00:08:52,040 --> 00:08:53,640
Haven't you ever wondered

110
00:08:54,480 --> 00:08:57,880
why he always gave in to you

111
00:08:58,480 --> 00:08:59,600
and did anything for you?

112
00:09:00,200 --> 00:09:04,040
He always showed
how much he cared about you.

113
00:09:05,840 --> 00:09:08,480
So… you two

114
00:09:09,640 --> 00:09:11,800
already knew?

115
00:09:11,880 --> 00:09:13,960
I just found out recently.

116
00:09:14,920 --> 00:09:17,520
I was the one who sent your DNA
and Uncle Pat's for testing.

117
00:09:18,960 --> 00:09:20,720
And the results confirmed it.

118
00:09:20,800 --> 00:09:23,560
Mrs. Sorn and Napat
had been in a relationship

119
00:09:24,080 --> 00:09:26,200
long before
she moved into Liangsuttha house.

120
00:09:26,280 --> 00:09:28,960
When she said
she was pregnant with my dad's child…

121
00:09:30,440 --> 00:09:32,320
she was probably pregnant with Napat's.

122
00:09:58,040 --> 00:10:00,320
The defendant ordered the killing
of many people,

123
00:10:02,400 --> 00:10:04,280
Jit, her trusted maid,

124
00:10:05,160 --> 00:10:06,040
Mrs. Kitinee,

125
00:10:07,280 --> 00:10:08,120
Mr. Terdthong,

126
00:10:11,320 --> 00:10:12,160
and Ms. Gingyok.

127
00:10:13,480 --> 00:10:15,560
I was the one who helped carry it all out.

128
00:10:20,880 --> 00:10:22,880
I want to apologize to all the victims.

129
00:10:24,320 --> 00:10:25,800
And I accept full responsibility

130
00:10:27,320 --> 00:10:29,080
for what I've done.

131
00:10:42,160 --> 00:10:43,240
Please take care of Nun for me.

132
00:10:52,400 --> 00:10:53,720
Ploy.

133
00:10:53,800 --> 00:10:56,640
You're so stupid
for falling for Ve's tricks.

134
00:10:56,720 --> 00:10:59,400
Don't think any of you can touch me.

135
00:11:01,120 --> 00:11:02,880
Please, Mrs. Sorn.

136
00:11:02,960 --> 00:11:04,520
After all this,

137
00:11:04,600 --> 00:11:07,240
you still feel no remorse
for all the people you've murdered?

138
00:11:08,320 --> 00:11:10,520
Ging shouldn't have met a person like you.

139
00:11:11,040 --> 00:11:14,520
Even your own daughter
can't accept what you did.

140
00:11:15,160 --> 00:11:17,000
Shouldn't that make you realize something?

141
00:11:20,200 --> 00:11:22,240
Don't let me get out of here!

142
00:11:22,320 --> 00:11:23,640
Calm down, Mrs. Sorn.

143
00:11:29,320 --> 00:11:30,680
Ki,

144
00:11:31,400 --> 00:11:33,040
is it wrong

145
00:11:34,520 --> 00:11:37,200
that I can't face either Mom or…

146
00:11:38,120 --> 00:11:39,360
Uncle Pat?

147
00:11:39,960 --> 00:11:41,000
You're not wrong.

148
00:11:41,080 --> 00:11:42,640
It's also my fault

149
00:11:42,720 --> 00:11:44,680
for hiding the truth
about Uncle Pat from you.

150
00:11:46,520 --> 00:11:50,560
Even now, I don't really know
how to feel about Mom.

151
00:11:52,200 --> 00:11:55,480
How could she do all of this?

152
00:11:56,160 --> 00:11:57,880
Did she ever stop to think

153
00:11:58,480 --> 00:12:00,320
about how we would feel?

154
00:12:00,840 --> 00:12:03,000
Did she ever care what we thought?

155
00:12:12,000 --> 00:12:13,160
Ms. Ve.

156
00:12:20,640 --> 00:12:21,960
I'm sorry, Ve.

157
00:12:23,200 --> 00:12:24,280
But…

158
00:12:24,360 --> 00:12:26,760
I feel so guilty
about what my mom did that…

159
00:12:28,440 --> 00:12:31,160
I just can't face you right now.

160
00:12:32,280 --> 00:12:33,120
I'm sorry.

161
00:12:43,160 --> 00:12:46,640
Even if Nun and I tried to repay you
for what our Mom did,

162
00:12:47,920 --> 00:12:49,120
it would never be enough.

163
00:12:51,280 --> 00:12:54,360
You and Nun
don't have to repay me anything.

164
00:12:55,560 --> 00:12:58,240
Because your mother
is about to atone for it herself.

165
00:12:59,120 --> 00:13:00,280
But regarding the case,

166
00:13:00,920 --> 00:13:03,280
she surely won't confess easily.

167
00:13:04,320 --> 00:13:06,160
It's going to be a long legal battle.

168
00:13:07,040 --> 00:13:09,800
My lawyer already told me
and Miss Ploy to brace ourselves.

169
00:13:10,520 --> 00:13:12,320
The case will drag on.

170
00:13:12,400 --> 00:13:15,040
But I've waited almost 20 years.

171
00:13:16,120 --> 00:13:19,000
Waiting a little longer
for justice from the court is fine.

172
00:13:32,160 --> 00:13:35,560
Thank you for coming along
to make merit for Prae and Teacher Rawee.

173
00:13:36,840 --> 00:13:39,760
And thank you
for bringing Napat to court today.

174
00:13:39,840 --> 00:13:42,880
Actually, it should've been Ki
who came with you.

175
00:13:43,520 --> 00:13:45,600
We're getting a divorce.

176
00:13:46,680 --> 00:13:49,040
I don't know what decision
you two ended up making…

177
00:13:50,400 --> 00:13:53,120
but I don't want to see
both of my beloved friends suffering.

178
00:13:54,440 --> 00:13:57,120
I truly hope you and Ki
will finally be happy together.

179
00:14:02,360 --> 00:14:03,760
Thank you, Mr. Pete.

180
00:14:13,040 --> 00:14:15,200
Miss Gingploy, what brings you here?

181
00:14:18,640 --> 00:14:20,920
Oh, I'm the one
who called and invited her.

182
00:14:21,440 --> 00:14:23,240
But she decided to show up late.

183
00:14:24,960 --> 00:14:27,240
Actually, I shouldn't have come.

184
00:14:32,280 --> 00:14:34,000
You'd better go after her.

185
00:14:34,640 --> 00:14:37,360
I want to see you
and Ploy happy together too.

186
00:14:45,400 --> 00:14:48,320
Hey, wait for me.

187
00:14:48,840 --> 00:14:51,960
You're late
and now you're leaving already?

188
00:14:52,040 --> 00:14:54,600
Why would I stay and get in your way?

189
00:14:54,680 --> 00:14:57,040
What? Hey, wait.

190
00:14:59,000 --> 00:15:02,400
If you want me to thank you
for reopening Ging's case,

191
00:15:02,480 --> 00:15:04,760
then fine. I'll thank you right here.

192
00:15:06,480 --> 00:15:09,160
Thank you. Satisfied now?

193
00:15:12,040 --> 00:15:12,840
Not yet.

194
00:15:13,960 --> 00:15:15,120
What else do you want?

195
00:15:15,800 --> 00:15:17,200
Besides a thank you…

196
00:15:18,360 --> 00:15:20,080
I want you by my side.

197
00:15:20,160 --> 00:15:22,280
Not just for today,

198
00:15:23,400 --> 00:15:25,000
but from now on

199
00:15:26,200 --> 00:15:27,320
until you get tired of me.

200
00:15:27,400 --> 00:15:28,880
What about Ve?

201
00:15:29,840 --> 00:15:31,680
She has nothing to do with this.

202
00:15:32,640 --> 00:15:34,040
She's my friend.

203
00:15:36,160 --> 00:15:37,720
But you…

204
00:15:40,000 --> 00:15:41,800
You're more than that.

205
00:15:43,240 --> 00:15:46,520
Honestly,
being by your side isn't a problem.

206
00:15:46,600 --> 00:15:49,160
But just so you know, I'm quite expensive.

207
00:15:50,800 --> 00:15:53,240
- Then I guess I'll go.
- Wait!

208
00:15:55,960 --> 00:15:57,760
In that case, give me a discount.

209
00:15:58,760 --> 00:16:00,040
Like 70% off?

210
00:16:00,120 --> 00:16:02,920
Who the hell bargains
with their girlfriend?

211
00:16:03,000 --> 00:16:04,120
You're so stingy.

212
00:16:17,080 --> 00:16:19,360
Ki. Nun.

213
00:16:19,440 --> 00:16:21,920
You don't have to worry.

214
00:16:22,000 --> 00:16:24,040
I'll be out soon.

215
00:16:24,120 --> 00:16:26,200
Don't worry. Once I'm out,

216
00:16:26,280 --> 00:16:29,400
I'll explain everything to you. Alright?

217
00:16:39,480 --> 00:16:41,200
No need.

218
00:16:42,400 --> 00:16:44,400
I came here today

219
00:16:45,160 --> 00:16:48,160
to tell you one last time

220
00:16:48,240 --> 00:16:51,040
that I won't come see you again.

221
00:16:53,920 --> 00:16:55,080
Why are you saying that?

222
00:16:55,160 --> 00:16:57,720
Because your crimes

223
00:16:58,320 --> 00:17:00,440
are too much.

224
00:17:00,520 --> 00:17:03,960
I don't know
how I can ever come to terms with them.

225
00:17:04,599 --> 00:17:06,480
And the fact that

226
00:17:06,560 --> 00:17:09,160
Uncle Pat is my real father.

227
00:17:10,359 --> 00:17:11,920
You lied to me,

228
00:17:12,599 --> 00:17:14,119
to everyone.

229
00:17:15,720 --> 00:17:16,800
But…

230
00:17:17,839 --> 00:17:20,240
everything I did,

231
00:17:21,200 --> 00:17:24,560
I did it for you, Nun, Ki.

232
00:17:25,200 --> 00:17:28,079
Back then, I was struggling.

233
00:17:28,160 --> 00:17:31,280
I didn't want my children
to struggle like I did.

234
00:17:32,640 --> 00:17:35,840
I wanted you to have everything,
just like everyone else.

235
00:17:36,520 --> 00:17:39,080
That's why I had to do all that.

236
00:17:40,480 --> 00:17:41,320
Dear,

237
00:17:42,400 --> 00:17:45,400
everything I did, I did for you.

238
00:17:47,560 --> 00:17:48,720
Mom.

239
00:17:49,560 --> 00:17:51,200
Please stop saying

240
00:17:51,280 --> 00:17:55,800
"I did it for you,"
to justify every horrible thing you did.

241
00:17:56,480 --> 00:17:58,160
Ki and I

242
00:17:59,360 --> 00:18:01,680
don't want anything more from you.

243
00:18:02,400 --> 00:18:04,640
I'm going to confess to the police

244
00:18:05,400 --> 00:18:07,520
about the hit-and-run I committed.

245
00:18:07,600 --> 00:18:09,600
I'll take full responsibility.

246
00:18:10,640 --> 00:18:12,720
I won't ask for any leniency.

247
00:18:14,040 --> 00:18:15,640
From now on,

248
00:18:17,120 --> 00:18:18,920
we won't be seeing each other again.

249
00:18:27,800 --> 00:18:30,280
Nun.

250
00:18:32,080 --> 00:18:33,880
Ki, wait. Wait.

251
00:18:33,960 --> 00:18:36,200
Ki, come back here. Come here.

252
00:18:36,920 --> 00:18:40,520
Ki, your sister's misunderstanding me.

253
00:18:40,600 --> 00:18:43,680
Please talk to her for me.

254
00:18:43,760 --> 00:18:45,080
Mom.

255
00:18:46,440 --> 00:18:47,840
I've already talked to her.

256
00:18:48,720 --> 00:18:51,520
But I can't change her mind.

257
00:18:53,520 --> 00:18:55,840
Still, I'll do my best to fix

258
00:18:57,480 --> 00:18:59,080
what you've done.

259
00:19:06,000 --> 00:19:09,760
Ki. Ki…

260
00:19:13,520 --> 00:19:14,880
My dear…

261
00:19:18,280 --> 00:19:21,000
I need to get out as soon as possible.
Is there a way?

262
00:19:21,080 --> 00:19:23,960
I have something important
to say to my children.

263
00:19:24,480 --> 00:19:27,800
I hired you. Do your job properly.

264
00:19:28,400 --> 00:19:30,960
- Actually, I've prepared everything.
- Alright.

265
00:19:31,680 --> 00:19:34,120
But this time,
you'll need to appear very ill.

266
00:19:35,440 --> 00:19:39,040
I'll arrange to have you transferred
to a hospital for treatment.

267
00:19:40,720 --> 00:19:41,680
What do I need to do?

268
00:19:49,720 --> 00:19:52,400
I've already filed
that you have a chronic illness

269
00:19:52,480 --> 00:19:54,560
and need regular medication.

270
00:19:56,840 --> 00:19:59,680
This medication will help you get outside.

271
00:20:56,920 --> 00:20:57,920
You should know

272
00:20:58,000 --> 00:21:01,200
how time flies in there.

273
00:21:01,280 --> 00:21:03,160
Ten years?

274
00:21:03,240 --> 00:21:06,960
It'll pass in a blink. She'll come out
like nothing ever happened.

275
00:21:07,040 --> 00:21:09,800
I feel bad for your only son.

276
00:21:10,800 --> 00:21:13,200
He had to die so pitifully because of her.

277
00:21:14,280 --> 00:21:16,720
I heard your granddaughter

278
00:21:16,800 --> 00:21:18,800
was also murdered by her.

279
00:21:19,600 --> 00:21:21,080
That's why I want to know,

280
00:21:21,600 --> 00:21:25,640
how can someone who suffered a loss
because of Kanisorn like I did

281
00:21:26,560 --> 00:21:27,840
just sit back and do nothing?

282
00:21:30,040 --> 00:21:34,080
Aren't you going to do anything
for your late son?

283
00:21:38,720 --> 00:21:39,760
Good question.

284
00:22:06,000 --> 00:22:08,600
Well, Grandma asked me to tell you

285
00:22:09,440 --> 00:22:11,680
she forgives Aunt Sorn.

286
00:22:14,640 --> 00:22:17,480
I forgive her too.

287
00:22:20,200 --> 00:22:22,200
On behalf of my mom, thank you.

288
00:22:25,920 --> 00:22:27,880
Such a quiet ceremony.

289
00:22:31,040 --> 00:22:33,720
I didn't even make it in time
for the ash scattering.

290
00:22:34,400 --> 00:22:36,320
You didn't have to come.

291
00:22:37,000 --> 00:22:40,520
Why not? If you can come, then so can I.

292
00:22:41,120 --> 00:22:43,280
Someone I knew just died.

293
00:22:43,360 --> 00:22:46,840
And I heard
she committed suicide in prison.

294
00:22:46,920 --> 00:22:49,200
Of course, I have to come pay my respects.

295
00:22:49,280 --> 00:22:51,600
Karma really worked fast, didn't it?

296
00:22:51,680 --> 00:22:53,440
Can you just stop?

297
00:22:55,360 --> 00:22:56,480
She's gone now.

298
00:22:58,000 --> 00:23:00,680
Is it really that hard to forgive?

299
00:23:02,720 --> 00:23:06,240
Didn't you say yourself
that karma works fast?

300
00:23:06,320 --> 00:23:07,720
Aren't you afraid it'll catch up to you?

301
00:23:09,240 --> 00:23:10,280
Oh.

302
00:23:11,040 --> 00:23:12,680
Or is it working now?

303
00:23:13,320 --> 00:23:16,200
I heard someone went bankrupt,

304
00:23:16,840 --> 00:23:18,360
ended up offering herself around,

305
00:23:18,960 --> 00:23:20,600
but no one took her.

306
00:23:23,280 --> 00:23:24,720
Gingploy.

307
00:23:24,800 --> 00:23:25,960
Mint.

308
00:23:27,080 --> 00:23:28,360
Thanks for coming.

309
00:23:29,320 --> 00:23:30,600
If there's nothing else,

310
00:23:31,320 --> 00:23:33,040
we'll take our leave.

311
00:23:33,760 --> 00:23:35,600
And hopefully,
we won't have to meet again.

312
00:23:39,160 --> 00:23:40,240
Let's go, Nun.

313
00:23:49,160 --> 00:23:50,480
As for me,

314
00:23:51,680 --> 00:23:54,040
If I ever said anything that upset you,

315
00:23:55,120 --> 00:23:57,040
I apologize.

316
00:24:00,000 --> 00:24:00,920
Next time,

317
00:24:02,400 --> 00:24:03,640
I'll do it again.

318
00:24:14,440 --> 00:24:16,720
How can your mouth be that vicious?

319
00:24:18,080 --> 00:24:19,200
And do you like it?

320
00:24:21,200 --> 00:24:22,120
Very much.

321
00:24:35,240 --> 00:24:38,880
Ms. Ve, once you sign this document,
all the assets,

322
00:24:38,960 --> 00:24:41,480
including the shares in the Suttha Group
of Mr. Kirin

323
00:24:42,480 --> 00:24:43,920
and Ms. Nunnalin

324
00:24:44,000 --> 00:24:46,400
will all belong to you.

325
00:24:46,480 --> 00:24:48,920
Nun and I are willingly
returning everything to you.

326
00:24:50,000 --> 00:24:52,840
Consider it me
fulfilling my promise to you.

327
00:24:53,840 --> 00:24:55,400
And what happens next?

328
00:24:56,960 --> 00:25:00,840
There's probably somewhere
I can start over with Kita.

329
00:25:01,960 --> 00:25:03,280
But it won't be far from here

330
00:25:03,360 --> 00:25:06,200
I still have to look after Nun
while she's serving her sentence.

331
00:25:09,800 --> 00:25:12,160
I guess I'll have to start over too.

332
00:25:13,000 --> 00:25:14,040
Please sign.

333
00:25:28,800 --> 00:25:30,520
It's all set.

334
00:25:35,880 --> 00:25:37,960
There's one more thing
I need to return to you.

335
00:26:10,720 --> 00:26:11,840
We're here. Let's go.

336
00:26:13,200 --> 00:26:14,400
Teacher Ve.

337
00:26:15,400 --> 00:26:16,520
Kita.

338
00:26:18,080 --> 00:26:21,760
Dad said you're leaving.
Where are you going?

339
00:26:21,840 --> 00:26:24,000
Kita, listen to me.

340
00:26:24,920 --> 00:26:26,560
One day,

341
00:26:27,120 --> 00:26:30,000
everyone has to go their own way.

342
00:26:30,720 --> 00:26:35,960
Just like you.
You're ready to start school now.

343
00:26:37,400 --> 00:26:40,080
You'll have new friends,

344
00:26:41,120 --> 00:26:43,360
new teachers to be with.

345
00:26:45,600 --> 00:26:48,520
And I also have a place I need to go.

346
00:26:49,680 --> 00:26:52,640
Will we ever see each other again?

347
00:26:54,040 --> 00:26:55,520
Of course we will.

348
00:26:56,760 --> 00:26:58,840
I love you.

349
00:27:00,040 --> 00:27:03,880
Besides Mom and Dad, I love you the most.

350
00:27:03,960 --> 00:27:06,240
And Dad loves you too.

351
00:27:15,080 --> 00:27:17,040
I love you too, Kita.

352
00:27:17,680 --> 00:27:20,760
And I love your dad very much as well.

353
00:27:33,040 --> 00:27:36,360
Then why can't people
who love each other be together?

354
00:28:15,440 --> 00:28:16,320
I have to go now.

355
00:29:15,840 --> 00:29:17,880
How are you doing today?

356
00:29:19,840 --> 00:29:22,080
I visited Uncle Pat for you,

357
00:29:23,080 --> 00:29:26,560
but he wouldn't see me.
He refuses to see anyone.

358
00:29:29,880 --> 00:29:31,120
Thank you

359
00:29:31,880 --> 00:29:33,320
for visiting

360
00:29:34,480 --> 00:29:35,920
my dad for me.

361
00:29:40,440 --> 00:29:41,320
But…

362
00:29:43,200 --> 00:29:44,880
aren't you tired,

363
00:29:46,200 --> 00:29:48,720
coming to visit me all the time?

364
00:29:49,880 --> 00:29:52,920
How could I be tired
when I'm visiting someone I love?

365
00:29:57,360 --> 00:29:59,760
But I don't want you to waste your time.

366
00:30:00,400 --> 00:30:01,520
Nun,

367
00:30:02,080 --> 00:30:06,120
time passes quickly. I can wait.

368
00:30:11,800 --> 00:30:13,280
Thank you.

369
00:30:13,960 --> 00:30:15,640
Other than Ki,

370
00:30:16,680 --> 00:30:18,120
you're the only one

371
00:30:19,440 --> 00:30:20,920
who's waiting for me to come out.

372
00:30:27,520 --> 00:30:29,640
No matter how long it takes,
I'll wait for you.

373
00:30:53,560 --> 00:30:56,920
Did you ask me out to eat
or to give you a massage?

374
00:30:57,760 --> 00:30:59,520
I'm tired.

375
00:30:59,600 --> 00:31:02,600
Ever since Ki handed over
all of Jade Biz to me,

376
00:31:02,680 --> 00:31:05,640
and Grandma's been sick
on and off every few days,

377
00:31:05,720 --> 00:31:08,080
I've been working alone like crazy.

378
00:31:08,160 --> 00:31:10,320
I'm exhausted.

379
00:31:11,000 --> 00:31:12,080
Aw…

380
00:31:12,760 --> 00:31:15,960
In that case, I guess
I'll have to postpone my proposal plan.

381
00:31:17,320 --> 00:31:19,040
You were going to propose?

382
00:31:20,920 --> 00:31:23,720
But you're so busy. Let's wait, okay?

383
00:31:24,840 --> 00:31:27,920
I can make time no matter how busy I am.

384
00:31:28,000 --> 00:31:30,840
And once I rest up,
I'll be able to take care of you too.

385
00:31:32,200 --> 00:31:33,760
But then again…

386
00:31:35,000 --> 00:31:36,920
didn't you say you were expensive?

387
00:31:38,240 --> 00:31:39,720
I probably can't afford you.

388
00:31:39,800 --> 00:31:42,680
I already gave you a 70% discount.

389
00:31:43,360 --> 00:31:46,560
How about this,
no interest, ten-month installment?

390
00:31:47,280 --> 00:31:49,240
You want to marry me that badly?

391
00:31:49,320 --> 00:31:50,720
Don't you?

392
00:31:50,800 --> 00:31:53,280
Guess I better prepare a wedding gift
for you and Ploy then.

393
00:31:55,520 --> 00:31:56,840
Ki.

394
00:32:02,600 --> 00:32:04,080
Wow.

395
00:32:07,080 --> 00:32:09,440
CEO of KMN Company?

396
00:32:10,120 --> 00:32:12,000
You started a new company
and didn't tell me?

397
00:32:12,080 --> 00:32:16,040
I just wanted to start over on my own.
And now I have.

398
00:32:16,120 --> 00:32:19,160
Congrats, new business owner.

399
00:32:19,240 --> 00:32:21,520
It's just a small company, Ploy.

400
00:32:22,120 --> 00:32:24,760
I'm sure someone as capable as you

401
00:32:24,840 --> 00:32:27,360
will make it a success.

402
00:32:35,960 --> 00:32:37,080
Hey, what is this?

403
00:32:40,800 --> 00:32:43,800
Oh, I didn't just

404
00:32:44,400 --> 00:32:46,280
want to know how you're doing.

405
00:32:47,800 --> 00:32:49,800
I also wanted to tell you
something about Ms. Ve.

406
00:32:51,000 --> 00:32:53,160
Ever since
you handed everything over to her,

407
00:32:54,520 --> 00:32:57,680
she's let the executive board
run the company.

408
00:32:58,320 --> 00:33:00,360
She hasn't gone back
to the Liangsuttha house either.

409
00:33:01,920 --> 00:33:03,240
I know that.

410
00:33:04,240 --> 00:33:06,520
Once I returned everything to her,

411
00:33:07,960 --> 00:33:11,000
I felt I shouldn't interfere
in her life anymore.

412
00:33:12,000 --> 00:33:16,080
Or maybe you just
didn't know where she was.

413
00:33:18,240 --> 00:33:21,240
She probably doesn't want
anyone interfering in her life,

414
00:33:22,080 --> 00:33:23,360
including me.

415
00:33:23,440 --> 00:33:25,560
What if I told you

416
00:33:26,320 --> 00:33:27,800
I know where she is?

417
00:33:32,520 --> 00:33:35,320
It's been a long time, Ki.

418
00:33:35,920 --> 00:33:37,120
I think

419
00:33:37,640 --> 00:33:40,880
you and Ve should follow your hearts now.

420
00:33:46,760 --> 00:33:48,800
TEACHER RAWEE'S ORPHANAGE

421
00:33:48,880 --> 00:33:50,840
"As time went by,

422
00:33:50,920 --> 00:33:52,880
everyone was overjoyed
that the princess had returned."

423
00:33:54,960 --> 00:33:57,000
"But the princess felt tired."

424
00:33:58,040 --> 00:33:59,520
"Even though the sadness had lifted,

425
00:34:00,600 --> 00:34:02,200
she wasn't fully healed."

426
00:34:04,120 --> 00:34:07,960
"Though the rose's thorns
had hurt and wounded her,

427
00:34:08,719 --> 00:34:11,920
she still thought of the rose always."

428
00:34:16,560 --> 00:34:19,639
"The princess returned to her own star,

429
00:34:19,719 --> 00:34:23,679
and saw roses blooming everywhere,

430
00:34:23,760 --> 00:34:25,000
just as promised."

431
00:34:27,159 --> 00:34:28,679
- "The rose was happy…"
- "The rose was happy

432
00:34:29,800 --> 00:34:31,360
to see the princess again."

433
00:34:43,199 --> 00:34:44,600
"And it told the princess that,

434
00:34:45,679 --> 00:34:47,480
'Waiting

435
00:34:48,199 --> 00:34:50,120
teaches us just how precious

436
00:34:51,040 --> 00:34:53,159
love and care truly are.'"

437
00:34:57,800 --> 00:35:00,240
I just read this story to Kita last night.

438
00:35:00,320 --> 00:35:02,040
He said he loved it

439
00:35:03,160 --> 00:35:06,240
because he wanted
to see the rose keep its promise.

440
00:35:08,560 --> 00:35:10,240
And he wanted to see

441
00:35:10,320 --> 00:35:13,480
the princess return to it once again.

442
00:35:22,240 --> 00:35:25,560
Teacher, can you tell us another story?

443
00:35:25,640 --> 00:35:27,000
- Please.
- Please.

444
00:35:27,080 --> 00:35:28,200
Please.

445
00:35:28,280 --> 00:35:29,840
Please.

446
00:35:29,920 --> 00:35:30,880
Sure.

447
00:35:42,280 --> 00:35:43,720
Let's go with this story.

448
00:35:49,520 --> 00:35:51,480
How did you know I was here?

449
00:35:52,000 --> 00:35:53,320
Pete and Ploy told me.

450
00:35:54,040 --> 00:35:57,320
All this time, I didn't know
if you even wanted to see me.

451
00:35:57,400 --> 00:36:00,760
But now, even if
you don't want to see me, I have to come.

452
00:36:01,840 --> 00:36:03,520
I can no longer lie to myself

453
00:36:04,040 --> 00:36:05,600
and pretend I'm okay without you.

454
00:36:11,320 --> 00:36:12,960
I used to think

455
00:36:13,960 --> 00:36:16,320
if I could get everything back,

456
00:36:16,400 --> 00:36:18,760
I'd be happy like before.

457
00:36:20,760 --> 00:36:24,080
But it only made me feel more alone.

458
00:36:25,120 --> 00:36:28,160
This place gave me a sense of community,

459
00:36:32,480 --> 00:36:35,640
but it's nothing
like being with you and Kita.

460
00:36:35,720 --> 00:36:37,440
Then why didn't you…?

461
00:36:37,520 --> 00:36:41,000
Because our story began
with lies and deception.

462
00:36:44,040 --> 00:36:46,040
I shouldn't go back to see you.

463
00:36:49,000 --> 00:36:50,840
I don't want to hurt you again.

464
00:36:58,600 --> 00:37:00,720
You've never hurt me.

465
00:37:02,280 --> 00:37:04,280
You know my feelings for you

466
00:37:05,000 --> 00:37:06,640
have always been real.

467
00:37:07,800 --> 00:37:10,240
There was never any lie or deceit.

468
00:37:19,760 --> 00:37:21,600
I want us to start over.

469
00:37:25,040 --> 00:37:26,440
No more lies,

470
00:37:26,960 --> 00:37:28,800
no more secrets.

471
00:37:30,440 --> 00:37:31,440
Can we?

472
00:37:35,280 --> 00:37:36,160
Yes.

473
00:37:36,880 --> 00:37:38,400
I won't lie to you.

474
00:37:40,160 --> 00:37:42,880
And I won't lie to myself anymore

475
00:37:44,960 --> 00:37:47,120
about how much I love you.

476
00:37:50,960 --> 00:37:52,320
I love you so much.

477
00:37:53,840 --> 00:37:56,480
Don't leave me again, Ms. Ve.

478
00:38:33,440 --> 00:38:36,400
THE END

479
00:41:33,480 --> 00:41:35,480
Subtitle translation by: Panuwat Baikeawon
